  "title": "On event example code given in the docs throws error in typescript",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nExample given in the docs throws error due to mismatched types\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the behavior:**\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/insights/js/#widget-param-onevent\r\n2. Copy and run the example code like this:\r\n```\r\ncreateInsightsMiddleware({\r\n  insightsClient: window.aa,\r\n  onEvent: (event, aa) => {\r\n    const { insightsMethod, payload } = event;\r\n\r\n    // Send the event to Algolia\r\n    aa(insightsMethod, payload);\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n4. You will see the error `Argument of type 'InsightsClientMethod | undefined' is not assignable to parameter of type 'InsightsClientMethod'.`\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\nCode compiles with no error \r\n\r\n<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n- OS: MacOs 12.2.1\r\n- Browser: Chrome 106\r\n\r\n",
